---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Case studies — Gian Trotta"
  description="Real before-and-after website rescues: measurable speed, search visibility, and cost results for small businesses."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Case studies</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-mist">
      Before-and-after, with real numbers. No stock screenshots, no vague claims.
    </p>

    <article class="mt-12 border border-line bg-white p-8">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare">Website Rescue</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 font-display text-2xl font-bold">
        Rusty the Raccoon — a children's book site, off Wix
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-mist">
        A children's book author was paying monthly for a slow Wix site that Google barely
        indexed. Rebuilt as a fast static site: sub-second loads, structured data, sitemap, Search
        Console — and a $0 hosting bill.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 font-utility text-sm text-mist">
        Full write-up with before/after numbers coming with launch.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="mt-6 border border-dashed border-line bg-porcelain p-8">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">In progress</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 font-display text-2xl font-bold text-mist">
        Fresh Beginnings Publishing — already fast, made findable
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-mist">
        A publisher's site with perfect speed scores that search engines and AI assistants barely
        knew existed. Refresh underway.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Base>
